				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">A few suggestions<a name="17279"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 26 04 7:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I can tell a lot of effort has gone into this site and I am very impressed.  However, I do have a few simple suggestions to make it even better.
<br />

<br />
- Change the color of the change password link on the my profile page.  It's the same color as the headings and I initially missed it scanning the page and ended up hunting around for a while.
<br />

<br />
- The bottom of the epic walkthrough guide has all the threads in the current epic forum.  I think it would be better to replace this with a link to that forum instead of showing the threads.  This would make it more printer friendly.
<br />

<br />
- I like the LDoN search.  I assume you will be adding an &quot;all dungeons&quot; selection.  If you can't for speed reasons, then perhaps having it for spells/songs only.  I find I need to look for where to buy a song/spell more often than what it actually does.
<br />

<br />
- Nice job on the songs page.  I would suggest adding a link to the page with Reed's spreadsheet at the top.
<br />

<br />
- In the class links page it would be nice to restructure the table so that the class sections line up in both columns.  You can also add beastlords.org (the site and forums opened after Yantis took over eqbeastlord.com) 
<br />

<br />
- A way of hiding the emotes in the post editor would be nice.  On slow machines the animations can really hurt the editor performance and not everyone will be using the computer they play EQ on to visit this site.
<br />

<br />
Great job and keep up the great work!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
