				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A few suggestions<a name="17287"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 26 04 7:52 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Gialla, thanks for the feedback!
<br />

<br />
1) Good point, I'll look into changing that.
<br />
2) I will be having a printer friendly version of the entire site soon, but it's not high on the priority list. I'm even going to have a PDA/mobile version!
<br />
3) The LDoN search was only an hour or so of work I did last night. Check it now, I added my work I did today. It now does &quot;All Dungeons&quot;, &quot;All Classes&quot;, and a few other things. I also plan to do a few more enhancements to that search.
<br />
4) Reed's spreadsheet is in the Files section. I have enough information going on in the Songs list page.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> I'm also working on Reed's spreadsheet online, although I want to finish up a few other things first.
<br />
5) The EQ links page is just a rough draft. I plan to make this a full-featured databased section where you can add your own links, rate them, see how many times they were clicked, etc... So this page will receive a huge revamp soon. I too did this in a few hours last week.
<br />
6) See above, the whole site is getting a &quot;Low Bandwidth&quot; and also a Printer-Friendly version when we get the new forums which I hope to get working next month.
<br />

<br />
So, in short, alot of the recent work has just been done in the past month. I will be spending more time with more features and improvements as the weeks go by.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /></span></td>
